        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "Rewrite: $\\frac{3x^4 - 2x}{x^2} = 3x^2 - 2x^{-1}$. Integrate: $3 \\cdot \\frac{x^3}{3} - 2\\ln|x| + C = x^3 - 2\\ln x + C$ (since $x > 0$)."
      },
