        ],
        "answer": "A",
        "explanation": "$f(x) = \\int (6x - 5) \\, dx = 3x^2 - 5x + C$. Use $f(1) = 4$: $3(1) - 5(1) + C = 4 \\Rightarrow -2 + C = 4 \\Rightarrow C = 6$. So $f(x) = 3x^2 - 5x + 6$."
